author: Achmad Firdaus
text:
It‚Äôs been close to a month since I took up the July promotional offer for membership at AF Mountbatten, and it has been a great re-introduction to being active and gymming again after a long break. The membership also allows 24/7 access to all AF gyms, locally and worldwide, and this has been great for flexibility and convenience.

Over at Mountbatten, the gym has a bright and welcoming atmosphere, with clean, well-maintained facilities and equipment that make workouts a lot more pleasant.

Special mention to Kim at the front desk for her warm professionalism, and to trainers Ross and Andi, who are knowledgeable, approachable, and always ready with practical advice on form and technique that makes workouts safer and more effective.

For anyone looking to kickstart or restart their fitness journey, AF Mountbatten is a fantastic choice.

author: Daniel Ng
text:
Went on a Friday night and around 8pm and the crowd was pretty quiet! It's a cosy space with equipment well laid out and the lighting is top notch, very bright. Not a plethora of machines, but enough to get a decent workout in. Unique thing about this AF are the Hammer Strength machines that most AFs don't have, personal favourite is the iso low row!

Slightly strange that the locker area is completely open so anyone at the power racks can see you there. Overall, super clean and well maintained equipment, a nice cosy gym.
